                                                "hideFigureSubCaption": false,
                                                "hideFigureFootnote": false,
                                                "markdown": "# Key Messages\n- Since the last Nigeria Demographic and Health Survey (NDHS) in 2024, ANC1,  ANC4, and institutional delivery coverage is estimated to have increased. This is a promising signal of progress in increasing access and utilization of maternal health services under the National Health Sector Renewal Initiative (NHSRII). \n- ANC4 coverage remains much lower than ANC1, highlighting the continued importance of registering women early for ANC and maintaining continuity of care. Most women are still booking for ANC 1 after 20 weeks.\n- Skilled birth attendance (SBA) and institutional delivery are increasing at the same rate; this shows that will service use is increasing, there has not been an increase in SBA availability. "
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ]
